        "title": "1985 Auto Imports Dataset (UCI ML Repository)",
        "subtitle": "The Corrected imports-85.data: NaN-Standardized + Pandas-Friendly",
        "description": "# Context\nThe 1985 Auto Imports Dataset captures a pivotal era in automotive history, documenting the shift toward fuel efficiency and globalization in car manufacturing. This dataset enables:\n* Analysis of 1980s automotive trends (MPG, engine tech, pricing)\n* Predictive modeling for insurance risk (symboling) and resale value\n\n# Overview\n| Category        | Detail                          |\n|-----------------|---------------------------------|\n| Records         | 205 records     |\n| Timeframe       | 1985        |\n| Manufacturers         | 22 brands (e.g., Toyota, BMW, Chevrolet)|\n| Features      | Price, MPG, horsepower, body style, fuel type |\n\n# Files\nMain Dataset (data.csv)\n* Standardized missing values (? \u2192 NaN)\n* Corrected dtypes (e.g., horsepower as float)\n* Original columns preserved with improved readability\n\n# Key Features\n1. Reliable dtypes: No more ValueError issues (fixed NaN and numeric columns).\n2. Historical Snapshot: Documents 1985 market trends (pre-NAFTA, pre-electronic engines).\n3. Machine Learning Ready: Cleaned for regression (predict price) or classification (e.g., fuel-type).\n4. Geographic Diversity: Mix of US, European, and Japanese manufacturers.\n\n# Uses\nThis dataset supports:\n* Price Prediction: Train models using engine size, MPG, and brand.\n* Risk Analysis: Correlate symboling with safety features.\n* Fuel Efficiency Studies: Compare 1985 MPG standards to modern EVs.\n* EDA Tutorials: Ideal for teaching pandas/seaborn (small but feature-rich).\n\n# Licensing\nLicense: [CC BY 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) (matches UCI\u2019s terms).\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nContains the same data provided by UCI after processing\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nsymboling: Index\nnormalized-losses: Insurance risk rating (-3 to +3), where +3 = high risk\nmake: Average insurance claim payout per vehicle (relative to other cars)\nfuel-type: Manufacturer (e.g., \"toyota\", \"bmw\")\naspiration: \"gas\" or \"diesel\"\nnum-of-doors: Engine air intake (\"std\" or \"turbo\")\nbody-style: \"two\" or \"four\"\ndrive-wheels: \"sedan\", \"hatchback\", \"wagon\", etc.\nengine-location: \"4wd\", \"fwd\" (front-wheel), \"rwd\" (rear-wheel)\nwheel-base: \"front\" or \"rear\"\nlength: Distance between wheels (inches)\nwidth: Vehicle dimensions (inches)\nheight: Vehicle dimensions (inches)\ncurb-weight: Vehicle dimensions (inches)\nengine-type: Weight without passengers (lbs)\nnum-of-cylinders: Engine design (e.g., \"ohc\", \"ohcv\")\nengine-size: \"two\", \"four\", \"six\", etc.\nfuel-system: Displacement volume (cubic inches)\nbore: Fuel delivery (e.g., \"mpfi\", \"2bbl\")\nstroke: Engine cylinder dimensions (inches)\ncompression-ratio: Engine cylinder dimensions (inches)\nhorsepower: Ratio of cylinder volume (high = more efficient)\npeak-rpm: Engine power (HP)\ncity-mpg: Engine speed at max power (RPM)\nhighway-mpg: Fuel efficiency (miles per gallon)\nprice: Fuel efficiency (miles per gallon)\n",
